The paper deals with improving the security of cognitive radio multicast communications, which involves information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), cryptography and security (cs.CR), multimedia (cs.MM), and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a cooperative approach to maximize the secrecy rate of the secondary system, which involves optimizing the beamforming strategy, and thus, falls under the above-mentioned sub-categories.
